# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Permanent Android release-signing secrets — TEMPLATE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy the four ANKAA_* lines below into your GLOBAL Gradle properties file
#   ~/.gradle/gradle.properties
# (NOT android/gradle.properties — that one is committed). Gradle reads
# findProperty('ANKAA_*') from ~/.gradle so the passwords never enter the repo.
#
# These MUST match exactly what you typed into scripts/generate-release-keystore.sh
# when the keystore was created. If you ever lose them you cannot re-sign with the
# same identity — App Links auto-verify would break until assetlinks.json is
# re-pinned to a new fingerprint. Back the keystore + these passwords up securely
# (password manager / encrypted vault).
#
# Store and key passwords MAY be identical, but keeping them distinct is fine too.

ANKAA_KEYSTORE_FILE=../../credentials/ankaa-release.keystore
ANKAA_KEY_ALIAS=ankaa
ANKAA_STORE_PASSWORD=replace-with-your-store-password
ANKAA_KEY_PASSWORD=replace-with-your-key-password
